					<h2><a title="Permanent Link to Abe’s Unwelcome Gift to Northeast Asia: A Visit to the Yasukuni Shrine" href="http://blog.keia.org/2013/12/abes-unwelcome-gift-to-northeast-asia-a-visit-to-the-yasukuni-shrine/" rel="bookmark">Abe’s Unwelcome Gift to Northeast Asia: A Visit to the Yasukuni Shrine</a></h2>
					<p class="post_date">Posted on 27 December 2013. <span class="singletags"></span></p>
		
					<div class="entry">
						<p>On December 26, Japan’s Prime Minister Abe Shinzo visited the Yasukuni Shrine. The visit is unlikely to do much harm to Abe domestically, but foreign policy in the region will be a casualty.</p>
							<p><span class="continue"><a title="Permalink to  Abe’s Unwelcome Gift to Northeast Asia: A Visit to the Yasukuni Shrine" href="http://blog.keia.org/2013/12/abes-unwelcome-gift-to-northeast-asia-a-visit-to-the-yasukuni-shrine/">Read the full story</a></span></p>
