				<div class="post-alt blog" id="post-2800">
		
					<a href="http://blog.keia.org/2013/12/employee-motivation-is-critical-to-creating-an-innovative-economy-and-jobs/" title="Employee Motivation is Critical to Creating an Innovative Economy and Jobs"><img src="https://i2.wp.com/blog.keia.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Workforce-by-Dells-Official-Flickr-Page-100x57.jpg" alt=""  width="100"  height="57"  class="woo-image th" /></a>                    
											
					<h2><a title="Permanent Link to Employee Motivation is Critical to Creating an Innovative Economy and Jobs" href="http://blog.keia.org/2013/12/employee-motivation-is-critical-to-creating-an-innovative-economy-and-jobs/" rel="bookmark">Employee Motivation is Critical to Creating an Innovative Economy and Jobs</a></h2>
					<p class="post_date">Posted on 04 December 2013. <span class="singletags">Tags: <a href="http://blog.keia.org/tag/economics/" rel="tag">economics</a></span></p>
		
					<div class="entry">
						<p>If Korean companies are able to exceed, or at a minimum match the world-wide average of an engaged workforce, government efforts to foster a creative economy will have a greater chance to succeed. </p>
							<p><span class="continue"><a title="Permalink to  Employee Motivation is Critical to Creating an Innovative Economy and Jobs" href="http://blog.keia.org/2013/12/employee-motivation-is-critical-to-creating-an-innovative-economy-and-jobs/">Read the full story</a></span></p>
